Retiring in 1990 from the position of Director of Evergreen-Tacoma, she continued to make a difference in the lives of young people. She founded the Maxine Mimms Academy, a non-profit dedicated to educating troubled students who have been cast out of public school environments.

Dr. Mimms made it her life-long work in the education sector as a teacher in Seattle and Tacoma. Her focus was on improving educational outcomes for African-American adults within urban areas. Maxine Mimms founded the Tacoma branch of Evergreen State College.

Hopefully the House will defeat it. But I hear the Senate is likely to defeat it and then Republicans will be forced to negotiate, forced to come to the table and actually do something that should have been done a long time age.

But we need to fund it, we need appropriations bills, not a continuing resolution. We are already 3 months plus into the fiscal year of 2018 without appropriations bills. We shouldn’t be passing CRs, we should be passing appropriations bills and we should be passing a DACA fix.

So, I’m voting no for that reason, but also a CR, a continuing resolution, is not funding the government. President Trump and the Republicans seem to think that the government really doesn’t matter, they don’t care about funding it.
